Structure of USB access code 

1.	Register with mid layer(USB Core) : Init function

2.	Init Power Mgmt operations:

 Probe function 

 Probe if device is found

3.	Set DMA address size (DMA mask)
    On chip DMA address

4.	Enable bus mastering

5.	Enable MSI/MSIx if supported

6.	Register ISR’s

7.	Access device system information

8.	Reserve / claim device address space


9.	Map device address space into kernel’s linear address [IOMEM]

10.	 Communicate with the device
